30% of the disease burden in India is attributable to infections. The hospital 
data constitute a basic and primary source of information for continuous follow 
up of this changing pattern of morbidity and mortality.
AIM: To identify the pattern and trend of different infectious diseases among 
admissions in the Infectious Disease ward of North Bengal Medical College and 
Hospital.
